Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine light red-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.181, 22). Name Andronikos. There would have been a caduceus symbol below the text. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum ABC 0316.34.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1034)
